<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,475,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific species name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[956,1037,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">testudo</emphasis>
” and refers to the characteristically shaped body of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[201,941,546,571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" box="[201,941,546,571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,546,571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Only one species in the genus. See diagnosis of genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" box="[201,655,582,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,346,582,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Description.</emphasis>
Total length 0.64–0.72 cm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,265,619,643]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Head</emphasis>
. Vertex: proportion A/B = 1.21–1.36; anterior margin (in dorsal view) strongly convex; lateral margins almost straight and parallel; posterior margin concave. Frons: proportion C/E = 0.63–0.67; proportion D/E = 1.00– 1.04. Frontoclypeal suture almost straight. Clypeus partly convex in median portion.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,290,727,751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum: proportion F/B = 1.02–1.16; anterior margin in median portion almost straight; posterior margin shallowly concave.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Mesonotum: proportion G/F = 2.18–2.36, proportion G/B+F = 1.16–1.25, proportion G/H = 0.80–0.86; scutellum with sharp apex.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" box="[201,616,870,894]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Tegmina: proportion I/J = 2.16–2.38.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,316,907,931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[381,479,906,930]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
was completely covered with white wax fibres, which melted under the heat of a lighting power supply.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,474,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,330,978,1003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Coloration</emphasis>
. General coloration from light to dark brown with yellowish patches, abdomen yellow to dirty yellow/muddy yellow, genital capsule a little darker; posterior margin of gonoplac and teeth dark brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
